1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,143
For years, the Transformer architecture and its self-attention

2
00:00:04,143 --> 00:00:07,952
mechanism have reigned supreme in deep learning. However,

3
00:00:07,952 --> 00:00:13,165
as sequence lengths scale, self-attention's quadratic computational complexity

4
00:00:13,165 --> 00:00:16,774
presents a critical bottleneck. State Space Models, or

5
00:00:16,774 --> 00:00:20,382
SSMs, have emerged as a powerful alternative, offering

6
00:00:20,382 --> 00:00:24,392
linear-time complexity with respect to sequence length while

7
00:00:24,392 --> 00:00:29,338
maintaining competitive performance. Grounded in classical control theory,

8
00:00:29,338 --> 00:00:32,479
these models map a continuous input sequence to

9
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:35,887
a continuous output sequence through a hidden state

10
00:00:35,887 --> 00:00:39,963
space. By combining the training efficiency of parallelizable

11
00:00:39,963 --> 00:00:43,840
convolutions with the inference speed of recurrent models,

12
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:47,248
modern SSMs are redefining the frontier of sequence

13
00:00:47,248 --> 00:00:51,391
modeling. Let's explore the mathematical foundation that makes

14
00:00:51,391 --> 00:00:53,663
this linear-time scaling possible.

15
00:00:53,664 --> 00:00:56,261
At the core of state space models are

16
00:00:56,261 --> 00:01:00,473
continuous-time differential equations. An input signal u of

17
00:01:00,473 --> 00:01:02,789
t is mapped to an output signal y

18
00:01:02,789 --> 00:01:05,527
of t by first projecting the input into

19
00:01:05,527 --> 00:01:09,247
an N-dimensional latent state x of t. Mathematically,

20
00:01:09,247 --> 00:01:11,845
the derivative of x with respect to t

21
00:01:11,845 --> 00:01:14,021
is equal to matrix A times x of

22
00:01:14,021 --> 00:01:16,057
t plus matrix B times u of t.

23
00:01:16,057 --> 00:01:18,443
The output y of t is then computed

24
00:01:18,443 --> 00:01:20,409
as matrix C times x of t. To

25
00:01:20,409 --> 00:01:24,340
process digital data, these continuous equations must be

26
00:01:24,340 --> 00:01:28,060
discretized using a step size delta. Through bilinear

27
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:32,413
discretization or zero-order hold, the continuous matrices are

28
00:01:32,413 --> 00:01:36,344
transformed into discrete matrices A-bar and B-bar. This

29
00:01:36,344 --> 00:01:39,854
allows the model to be computed either recurrently

30
00:01:39,854 --> 00:01:44,346
for ultra-fast, constant-time inference, or convolutionally as a

31
00:01:44,346 --> 00:01:46,944
single parallel pass during training.

32
00:01:46,944 --> 00:01:50,297
While classical SSMs like S4 excel at long-range

33
00:01:50,297 --> 00:01:55,467
dependencies, they struggle with content-dependent reasoning tasks because

34
00:01:55,467 --> 00:01:59,310
their transition matrices are static and independent of

35
00:01:59,310 --> 00:02:02,454
the input tokens. Mamba, introduced by Gu and

36
00:02:02,454 --> 00:02:06,576
Dao, addresses this limitation by making the discretization

37
00:02:06,576 --> 00:02:09,720
step delta, and the projection matrices B and

38
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:12,654
C, dynamic functions of the input token at

39
00:02:12,654 --> 00:02:16,846
each step. This input-dependent selectivity allows the model

40
00:02:16,846 --> 00:02:20,689
to selectively remember or forget information along the

41
00:02:20,689 --> 00:02:25,929
sequence. However, dynamic matrices break the convolutional parallelization

42
00:02:25,929 --> 00:02:30,121
property. To maintain training efficiency, Mamba leverages a

43
00:02:30,121 --> 00:02:35,710
hardware-aware parallel associative scan, streaming intermediate states directly

44
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:39,064
through fast GPU SRAM and avoiding slow off-chip

45
00:02:39,064 --> 00:02:40,392
memory write-backs.

46
00:02:40,391 --> 00:02:44,766
Building on Mamba, Mamba-2 introduces Structured State Space

47
00:02:44,766 --> 00:02:48,849
Duality, or SSD, which establishes a formal mathematical

48
00:02:48,849 --> 00:02:53,442
connection between selective SSMs and attention mechanisms. SSD

49
00:02:53,442 --> 00:02:56,359
shows that selective SSMs can be cast as

50
00:02:56,359 --> 00:03:00,369
semi-separable matrices, which compute a form of linear

51
00:03:00,369 --> 00:03:04,233
attention where the key-value states are decayed over

52
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:07,586
time by the transition matrix. By framing SSMs

53
00:03:07,586 --> 00:03:11,596
as dual attention formulations, Mamba-2 enables the use

54
00:03:11,596 --> 00:03:16,263
of tensor parallelism and highly optimized matrix multiplication

55
00:03:16,263 --> 00:03:19,908
kernels. This dual framework achieves two to eight

56
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:24,137
times faster training and inference throughput compared to

57
00:03:24,137 --> 00:03:28,366
Mamba-1, merging the theoretical scaling benefits of state

58
00:03:28,366 --> 00:03:32,375
space models with the hardware efficiency of attention.

59
00:03:32,376 --> 00:03:36,741
The evolution from standard self-attention to Structured State

60
00:03:36,741 --> 00:03:40,121
Space Duality marks a profound shift in sequence

61
00:03:40,121 --> 00:03:44,416
representation. By combining linear time and space complexity

62
00:03:44,416 --> 00:03:49,203
with dynamic, content-dependent selectivity, Mamba and Mamba-2 offer

63
00:03:49,203 --> 00:03:53,921
a scalable alternative to traditional Transformers for long-context

64
00:03:53,921 --> 00:03:58,427
applications. To continue exploring the mathematical details and

65
00:03:58,427 --> 00:04:02,581
physical hardware co-designs behind modern AI, subscribe to

66
00:04:02,581 --> 00:04:05,890
Gemini three point five Flash Model. Let's keep

67
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:08,496
optimizing the future of computation.
